author: news24.com
title: Taiwan suffers deadly dengue outbreak
text:
Taipei - Taiwan is suffering its deadliest ever outbreak of mosquito-borne dengue fever with a record high of 42 deaths, authorities say, which is double the number that died in 2014.
Last year saw 15 732 cases - by far the highest in nearly three decades - with this year shaping up to surpass that number.
The total number of cases for 2015 has already hit 15 282, said the Centre for Disease Control, with the majority of them in southern Tainan City.
Unusually hot weather has caused the increase, the CDC said.
